{
  "texts": [
    "In summary, DART-FISH is a reproducible spatial transcriptomic method with the sensitivity and specificity to detect hundreds of RNA species in their spatial context, with the potential for providing biologically meaningful insights to the human brain despite the high natural background autofluorescence.",
    "Fig. 1 | DART-FISH workflow.",
    "a Schematics of DART-FISH.",
    "RNA molecules in a fresh-frozen and formaldehyde-fixed tissue section were reverse-transcribed with primers carrying a 5' handle with an acrydite modification.",
    "A polyacrylamide (PA) gel was cast on the tissue, incorporating the cDNA molecules in the gel matrix."
  ]
}